<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5219214>
    dc:description "Figure 13. Polysyncraton dealbatum sp. nov. (QM G328119). A, larva. Polysyncraton fistulum sp nov. (QM G328446): B, colony; C, crosssection through colony lobe; D, longitudinal section through part of colony lobe showing hard rods of crowded spicules forming skeletal support; E, larva. Polysyncraton millepore (F, QM G328050; G, QM G328033): F, portion of colony showing ripple marks on undersurface; G, zooid. Polysyncraton pavementum (QM G328058): H, surface of colony showing separate systems. Scales: A, E, G, 0.2 mm; B, 2.0 cm; C, H, 3.0 mm; D, 1.0 cm; F, 3.0 cm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5219214/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5219220>
    dc:description "Figure 16. Scanning electron micrographs of didemnid spicules: A, Atriolum tubiporum, QM G328004; B, Leptoclinides durus, QM G328158; C, Leptoclinides fungiformis, QM G328444; D, Leptoclinides vesica, QM G328458; E, F, Polysyncraton calculum, QM G328140; G, Polysyncraton dealbatum, QM G328119; H, Polysyncraton fistulum, QM G328446." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5219220/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

